reviews.text: The food is too good. I came for the $4 Asahi and left with a belly full of amazing, freshly cooked tapas with fresh ingredients and wonderfully balanced flavour. Youâ€™d pay 4x the price in Australia for the quality of food and 10x the price in London, assuming you could find it.

Great place for chillout and gatherings, had a dozen beers plus multiple rounds of cocktails and shots. Had quite a great night although the they miss out on my friends cocktails a couple of times even after repeatly asking till the 3rd time then it came and it happens for a few subsequent orders.

The atmosphere in here is very cozy , relaxed and giving  very lively vibes. The food is so delicious. All the dishes tastes so good. Cucumber salad is all time my favourite. The service from the staffs is very pleasant ,friendly and well recognisable. Special thanks to Arkar who is polite and has an excellent service.

Kanpai is the more popular ones among Robertson area for drinks and food. They are popular for a reason, fast service , food have to wait a little but they have nice concept of beer O clock and decent cocktails, beer choices and etc. I love their Shio Bak and La zi Ji! Sometimes, atmosphere can be rowdy from the drinking crowd .

Came here for chillax and i must say they have great variety for beer food. Freshness gauranteed and doesnt disappoint. Food amd drinks can be slightly on the slower side to be served during peak hour but i think its worth the wait.
